00:44:59,897 --> 00:45:01,421
Water is all that I want.

743
00:45:01,965 --> 00:45:03,899
- Really?
- Nothing else.

744
00:45:04,001 --> 00:45:06,561
Hey man, you could have said so.

745
00:45:07,171 --> 00:45:09,071
- Chucho!
- Yes master?

746
00:45:10,541 --> 00:45:12,221
Bring this gentleman a
big bottle of water.

747
00:45:15,913 --> 00:45:17,380
Here you are, master.

748
00:45:20,217 --> 00:45:21,217
Here you are.

749
00:45:22,219 --> 00:45:23,311
Thank you, sir!

750
00:45:23,787 --> 00:45:25,448
Are you leaving again?

751
00:45:25,689 --> 00:45:27,452
No, I'm staying as a tourist.

752
00:45:28,392 --> 00:45:30,826
To see if I can take
from Jorge...

753
00:45:30,894 --> 00:45:32,862
something else besides
his money.

754
00:45:41,271 --> 00:45:42,602
Have many days like today...

755
00:45:42,706 --> 00:45:44,173
Thank you, Madam.

756
00:45:45,209 --> 00:45:45,937
Congratulations.

757
00:45:46,009 --> 00:45:48,068
Thank you.
Ok, let's go walking.

758
00:45:53,050 --> 00:45:55,314
Your dress is so beautiful!
Do you like it?

759
00:45:55,385 --> 00:45:56,647
It was dad's gift.

760
00:45:56,754 --> 00:45:59,086
One of them, because you haven't
seen the main one.

761
00:45:59,156 --> 00:46:02,387
This aftenoon's party. Such a
big party to be remembered!

762
00:46:02,459 --> 00:46:05,587
- Isn't that Jorge?
- General, as everything you organize.

763
00:46:05,662 --> 00:46:08,187
Well, I leave you beacause I have
to go to the station to pick up...

764
00:46:08,298 --> 00:46:10,528
a very special cognac. Excuse
me, good afternoon.

765
00:46:10,634 --> 00:46:12,602
See you later General.

766
00:46:15,906 --> 00:46:18,170
My good frieng. I didn't
expect you here!

767
00:46:18,275 --> 00:46:20,573
How do you do, General.
I'm at your service.

768
00:46:20,677 --> 00:46:24,773
Listen Pedrito. I expect you by 6 in
my house. It's my daughter's bithday.

769
00:46:26,316 --> 00:46:29,410
I guess Jorge and his family
will be there, don't they?

770
00:46:29,520 --> 00:46:31,112
Of course.

771
00:46:31,555 --> 00:46:33,352
- You must be there!
- Of course general.

772
00:46:33,457 --> 00:46:35,049
I'm not used to miss
such events.

773
00:46:35,159 --> 00:46:37,593
- Count me on.
- Ok, see you later.

774
00:46:40,998 --> 00:46:41,998
Pedro.

775
00:46:44,234 --> 00:46:46,930
- Come here.
- Damn!

776
00:46:51,341 --> 00:46:53,741
- What are you doing here?
- You're surprised, aren't you?

777
00:46:53,811 --> 00:46:57,406
Last time we argued, I said
you were a bad man...

778
00:46:57,514 --> 00:47:01,177
miserable tyrant of my daughter,
I said everything!

779
00:47:01,251 --> 00:47:02,946
And to repeat that, you
bother yourself to come!

780
00:47:03,020 --> 00:47:07,013
Let me tell you everything I've gotta
say, and then you speak, ok?

781
00:47:07,124 --> 00:47:08,124
Ok.

782
00:47:08,625 --> 00:47:10,525
The problems have with
your father-in-law...

783
00:47:10,594 --> 00:47:13,028
...are not for you to abandon
your wife and daughter!

784
00:47:13,096 --> 00:47:15,963
Oh shit! Why do you say that
I have abandoned them?

785
00:47:16,033 --> 00:47:21,403
Isn't it abandonment to desert without
conset and stay a far away?

786
00:47:21,505 --> 00:47:24,303
No sir! I have to work out
an urgent problem here.

787
00:47:24,408 --> 00:47:26,933
It is also very urgent to
meet your family's needs!

788
00:47:27,044 --> 00:47:29,478
That's why I brougth Rosario
and the baby this way!

789
00:47:29,580 --> 00:47:30,808
- They're here?
- Yes sir!

790
00:47:30,914 --> 00:47:32,677
Damn! Why did you
bring them here?

791
00:47:32,749 --> 00:47:36,549
Because you musn't show off as a
bachelor. You're married, sir!

792
00:47:36,653 --> 00:47:39,178
No sir! You're going back
to town right away!

793
00:47:39,289 --> 00:47:42,349
You're wrong son! From now
on, wherever you go...

794
00:47:42,459 --> 00:47:44,689
even to hell, your wife and your
daughter will go with you.

795
00:47:44,761 --> 00:47:46,558
No, no, no sir!

796
00:47:46,663 --> 00:47:48,654
- You'll see, uncle.
- I'm not your uncle.

797
00:47:48,732 --> 00:47:50,666
Unfortunately, I'm
your father-in-law!

798
00:47:50,734 --> 00:47:54,261
You don't seem so. You seem
to be a nosy mother-in-law!

799
00:47:54,571 --> 00:47:57,472
Oh yeah? That's what
I look like for you?

800
00:47:58,041 --> 00:48:01,909
Tomorrow I'll go to Veracruz
to take a ship...

801
00:48:02,012 --> 00:48:04,845
and I'll go to my homeland. You
stay here with your wife,

802
00:48:04,948 --> 00:48:06,438
...and we'll se how you
manage with her...

803
00:48:06,550 --> 00:48:10,919
Will anybody look after her like me?
I have even neglected my business.

804
00:48:11,288 --> 00:48:15,224
It's up to you! Do you want the
nosy mother-in-law to leave?

805
00:48:15,325 --> 00:48:17,088
Don't do that uncle, don't go.

806
00:48:17,160 --> 00:48:19,025
What will Rosarito
do without you?

807
00:48:19,096 --> 00:48:21,189
That's what I say sir.

808
00:48:21,498 --> 00:48:26,197
If you're a good boy with a great
heart, why don't you well behave?

809
00:48:26,303 --> 00:48:29,568
Behave well with my daghter, and
you'll have everything with me.

810
00:48:29,640 --> 00:48:32,837
Not money, but lots
of friendship.

811
00:48:32,943 --> 00:48:35,639
Why do you have to be arguing
with me all the time?

812
00:48:36,613 --> 00:48:40,049
Let's go to you hotel to check
out and we'll go home.

813
00:48:40,984 --> 00:48:41,984
What home?

814
00:48:42,085 --> 00:48:46,351
Have you forgoten, Pedrito, that
we have our abandoned house here?

815
00:48:46,690 --> 00:48:49,853
Ok. Let's go home, sir.

816
00:48:49,927 --> 00:48:53,363
More respect for your
father-in law, Pedro.

817
00:48:54,731 --> 00:48:57,894
You're so funny, really.

818
00:48:57,968 --> 00:48:59,936
We'll go in a minute, doctor,
don't be impatient.

819
00:49:00,003 --> 00:49:02,904
- I'm not in a hurry, Josefa.
- Anastasia!

820
00:49:03,807 --> 00:49:05,434
What happend with my tie?

821
00:49:05,509 --> 00:49:07,306
- What's up doctor.
- It's here!

822
00:49:07,377 --> 00:49:09,277
Do you know who arrived at noon?

823
00:49:09,379 --> 00:49:12,815
- Who?
- Who else can it be? Rosario.

824
00:49:13,216 --> 00:49:16,413
She's not that young.
She has a baby.

825
00:49:16,520 --> 00:49:19,216
- Is she married to Mr. Pedro?
- Shut up!

826
00:49:21,825 --> 00:49:25,420
Anastasia, you musn't mention
those names in this house!

827
00:49:25,495 --> 00:49:28,430
- This shall be the last time!
- Yes Madam.

828
00:49:40,477 --> 00:49:42,342
You still love her, don't you?

829
00:49:47,017 --> 00:49:48,985
- No, I don't.
- You don't fool me.

830
00:49:49,353 --> 00:49:51,514
You're still in love
with Rosario.

831
00:49:51,722 --> 00:49:54,953
Not in love.
I'm ill.

832
00:49:56,593 --> 00:50:00,495
It's a chronic illness that goes and
comes back when you least expect it.

833
00:50:00,630 --> 00:50:03,690
There's a song for that illness.

834
00:50:04,034 --> 00:50:05,626
A spoon of oblivion...

835
00:50:05,969 --> 00:50:08,028
and drops from another love.

836
00:50:08,238 --> 00:50:11,298
Yeah, my prescription is
a wedding with Genoveva.

837
00:50:12,376 --> 00:50:15,971
Let's see if insted of
a spoon, it's a rub!

838
00:50:17,247 --> 00:50:20,239
You'll go to the doctor's.
I'll meet you there.

839
00:50:24,154 --> 00:50:27,351
We have a beautiful baby here.

840
00:50:37,534 --> 00:50:42,369
...tha beautifil baby we have
here. Look at the pigeons.

841
00:50:42,572 --> 00:50:45,234
Look at them. Don't you
want to see them?

842
00:50:48,011 --> 00:50:50,104
We have more pigeons
here baby...

843
00:50:50,914 --> 00:50:52,108
See you later, Chayo.

844
00:50:52,783 --> 00:50:53,943
Won't you stay for lunch?

845
00:50:54,051 --> 00:50:57,578
I have to go with some friends.
Business lunch.

846
00:50:57,687 --> 00:51:00,713
- See you tomorrow, Mr. Elias.
- See you tomorrow?

847
00:51:00,791 --> 00:51:03,351
Does it mean you're
coming back at dawn?

848
00:51:03,427 --> 00:51:05,361
Or by day. You
can nver know.

849
00:51:05,462 --> 00:51:07,828
Have you seen, baby?

850
00:51:07,898 --> 00:51:11,493
You cannot keep your mouth closed
with a man like this.

851
00:51:11,635 --> 00:51:14,001
He's a carouser, shameless.

852
00:51:14,271 --> 00:51:17,468
But to avoid your grandpa been
called a nosy mother-in-law...

853
00:51:17,541 --> 00:51:20,203
We put on my lips a patch.

854
00:51:20,610 --> 00:51:22,009
And we can deal with
the carouser.

855
00:51:22,145 --> 00:51:23,373
There you go again, dad?

856
00:51:23,480 --> 00:51:26,677
I'm saying nothig, but talking
to my grandchild.

857
00:51:26,750 --> 00:51:29,378
See you tomorrow
Pedrito. Do well.

858
00:51:29,986 --> 00:51:32,147
Son of my heart.

859
00:51:54,911 --> 00:51:56,344
Try not to come back
late, Pedro.

860
00:51:56,413 --> 00:51:58,313
I don't want my dad
to start talking.

861
00:51:58,381 --> 00:52:00,645
Don't worry for your
husband, Madam.

862
00:52:00,750 --> 00:52:01,750
Pedro!

863
00:52:10,527 --> 00:52:11,527
Jorge!

864
00:52:17,767 --> 00:52:19,234
Aren't you ashamed to see me?

865
00:52:20,337 --> 00:52:21,337
I don't think so!

866
00:52:22,205 --> 00:52:25,003
If you were ashamed, you
wouldn't have come.

867
00:52:25,675 --> 00:52:26,733
Jorge, please.

868
00:52:27,077 --> 00:52:29,170
I feel sorry for you.

869
00:52:30,013 --> 00:52:33,540
When a woman like you and a man
like him are join by betrayal...

870
00:52:34,050 --> 00:52:35,813
they always finish the same.

871
00:52:36,052 --> 00:52:37,644
She cheats on her husband.

872
00:52:37,821 --> 00:52:40,221
And him, abandoning her!

873
00:52:40,790 --> 00:52:41,882
It never fails!

874
00:52:43,960 --> 00:52:46,224
<i>You are, darling...</i>

875
00:52:46,296 --> 00:52:49,163
<i>who got me in ecstasies..</i>

876
00:52:49,466 --> 00:52:54,062
<i>Why should I deny that
I'm in love with you?</i>

877
00:52:54,437 --> 00:52:57,565
<i>From your sweet soul</i>

878
00:52:57,641 --> 00:53:01,941
<i>that is full of feelings.</i>

879
00:53:03,914 --> 00:53:10,012
<i>With those black eyes with
a strange shining.</i>

880
00:53:10,554 --> 00:53:15,253
<i>That control me and demand
me to love you.</i>

881
00:53:15,325 --> 00:53:21,355
<i>You're my delight,
you're my illusion.</i>

882
00:53:24,401 --> 00:53:28,201
<i>I know that glory...</i>

883
00:53:28,271 --> 00:53:31,434
<i>is in Heaven...</i>

884
00:53:33,743 --> 00:53:37,975
<i>and is to mortals...</i>

885
00:53:38,048 --> 00:53:42,951
<i>the hope when they die.</i>

886
00:53:43,286 --> 00:53:49,191
<i>I bless God because having
you in lifetieme...</i>

887
00:53:49,259 --> 00:53:52,990
<i>I don't need to go to Heaven.</i>

888
00:53:53,096 --> 00:53:56,259
<i>Yes darling,</i>

889
00:53:57,667 --> 00:54:02,764
<i>you're the Glory...</i>

890
00:54:10,380 --> 00:54:12,644
Sorry to be a little
late. Good afternoon.

891
00:54:12,983 --> 00:54:16,043
Don't worry. You're
just in time.

892
00:54:16,486 --> 00:54:18,010
Please come in.

893
00:54:18,288 --> 00:54:21,815
We'll drink a cognac that is not
a cognac, it's a Heaven's gift!

894
00:54:28,098 --> 00:54:30,464
- What are you doing here?
- I was invited.

895
00:54:31,534 --> 00:54:32,534
Sponger!

896
00:54:36,506 --> 00:54:38,440
Ladies and Gentlemen...

897
00:54:39,542 --> 00:54:41,772
I want to officialy announce...

898
00:54:41,878 --> 00:54:46,178
my daughter's engagement
to Mr. Jorge Bueno...

899
00:54:46,316 --> 00:54:49,285
who has honored me
to ask her hand...

900
00:54:49,452 --> 00:54:53,548
and I will tell you that
I congratulate myself...

901
00:54:53,657 --> 00:54:56,091
because without offending
those of you here...

902
00:54:56,159 --> 00:54:59,617
I wouldn't find a
better son-in-law.

903
00:55:06,169 --> 00:55:08,729
Bravo! Good!

904
00:55:11,741 --> 00:55:14,869
Now you pay compliments
to the happy couple.

905
00:55:14,978 --> 00:55:16,946
I was ready for it!

906
00:55:18,448 --> 00:55:20,712
Ready guys!

907
00:55:23,820 --> 00:55:25,185
Let's start!

908
00:55:27,590 --> 00:55:30,058
<i>People honestly say...</i>

909
00:55:30,293 --> 00:55:35,060
<i>in every wedding</i>

910
00:55:35,865 --> 00:55:41,167
<i>bridegroom always love her,
but to have his funeral...</i>

911
00:55:42,305 --> 00:55:48,471
<i>this bride has no sorrow, because
she 'll have a good husband.</i>

912
00:55:48,578 --> 00:55:53,709
<i>Jorge Bueno is a good thing,
at least his last name...</i>

913
00:55:54,617 --> 00:55:56,915
<i>Jorge Bueno is very good...</i>

914
00:55:57,087 --> 00:55:59,317
<i>son of Bueno too...</i>

915
00:55:59,422 --> 00:56:02,084
<i>and his grandfather, very good,</i>

916
00:56:02,192 --> 00:56:04,558
<i>that had his name.</i>

917
00:56:10,433 --> 00:56:12,526
Play for me, but a little higher.

918
00:56:14,237 --> 00:56:21,405
<i>I'll try to be as good
as my last name...</i>

919
00:56:22,245 --> 00:56:27,444
<i>let him drink his poison who
has demanded a funeral...</i>

920
00:56:28,451 --> 00:56:30,976
<i>Pedro has a bad last name.</i>

921
00:56:31,054 --> 00:56:34,182
<i>I'll answer to his verses.</i>

922
00:56:34,758 --> 00:56:38,489
<i>He only wants to show off,
because he isn't bad, is...</i>

923
00:56:39,162 --> 00:56:41,062
<i>hopeless.</i>

924
00:56:41,965 --> 00:56:44,433
<i>Pedro Malo is very bad...</i>

925
00:56:44,801 --> 00:56:46,928
<i>bad by destiny...</i>

926
00:56:47,036 --> 00:56:49,231
<i>and his gandfather, uy!
What a bad guy...</i>

927
00:56:49,339 --> 00:56:52,433
<i>we got to buy him a lion.</i>

928
00:56:57,147 --> 00:56:58,944
<i>On a sunny morning...</i>

929
00:56:59,015 --> 00:57:04,920
<i>sombody clouded the landscape...</i>

930
00:57:05,722 --> 00:57:10,557
<i>there were a crow and a parrot
tearing out their feathers.</i>

931
00:57:12,095 --> 00:57:17,226
<i>You've got to forget the past,
if luck is guilty...</i>

932
00:57:18,368 --> 00:57:21,667
<i>Good and Bad mixed...</i>

933
00:57:22,405 --> 00:57:25,135
<i>turn out mediocre.</i>

934
00:57:25,208 --> 00:57:27,733
<i>I'm bad, don't deny it...</i>

935
00:57:28,144 --> 00:57:32,774
<i>but I'd like to mix Good
and Bad to see...</i>

936
00:57:32,849 --> 00:57:35,147
<i>if you get something fair.</i>

937
00:57:39,489 --> 00:57:41,650
Please do something. Those
guys are going to fight.

938
00:57:43,393 --> 00:57:45,987
<i>Easy you scaveger scorpion...</i>

939
00:57:46,095 --> 00:57:52,193
<i>you were visiting an apiary...</i>

940
00:57:52,836 --> 00:57:59,071
<i>to see if poison could
be removed with honey</i>

941
00:57:59,175 --> 00:58:05,045
<i>and goodness is not for evil...</i>

942
00:58:06,249 --> 00:58:10,276
<i>with honey and his poison,
today he's...</i>

943
00:58:10,954 --> 00:58:13,218
<i>purged!</i>

944
00:58:13,323 --> 00:58:16,486
<i>Let him be understood,
who can understand him...</i>

945
00:58:16,559 --> 00:58:19,050
<i>if he can be understood...</i>

946
00:58:19,128 --> 00:58:22,029
<i>and if he can't understand...</i>

947
00:58:22,131 --> 00:58:25,328
<i>he's got to be forced to understand.</i>

948
00:58:26,569 --> 00:58:28,036
I'm going to tell the
orchestra to play.

949
00:58:28,137 --> 00:58:29,137
Why?

950
00:58:30,740 --> 00:58:34,699
<i>It is clear to you that I'm
not a fool like you...</i>

951
00:58:35,712 --> 00:58:38,681
<i>has showed...</i>

952
00:58:39,582 --> 00:58:41,777
<i>Not a fool, but a meddler...</i>

953
00:58:41,885 --> 00:58:43,853
<i>for your hunger...</i>

954
00:58:44,954 --> 00:58:47,752
<i>of friends.</i>

955
00:58:48,324 --> 00:58:53,660
<i>I always calm my hunger
with my friend's food...</i>

956
00:58:55,164 --> 00:59:00,261
<i>Beggar, but a beggar who
steals his friends...</i>

957
00:59:01,437 --> 00:59:02,437
<i>You say so.</i>

958
00:59:02,739 --> 00:59:04,036
<i>I stand for it!</i>

959
00:59:04,107 --> 00:59:06,234
<i>Don't be tired...</i>

960
00:59:06,409 --> 00:59:08,536
<i>- Don't avoid it!
- I avoid it.</i>

961
00:59:08,611 --> 00:59:10,579
<i>Then this song is over!</i>

962
00:59:12,148 --> 00:59:13,911
- Do you dance, Jorge?
- Later.

963
00:59:14,017 --> 00:59:15,507
Let's dance, please.

964
00:59:17,387 --> 00:59:18,387
Later.

965
00:59:27,530 --> 00:59:29,259
They're so playful.

966
00:59:34,203 --> 00:59:35,203
Maruca!

967
00:59:40,310 --> 00:59:41,868
Why don't you say hello?

968
00:59:42,278 --> 00:59:43,278
Who are you?

969
00:59:44,080 --> 00:59:47,811
The same "Periquito" who loves
you more everyday...

970
00:59:48,651 --> 00:59:49,811
Oh yes...

971
00:59:50,153 --> 00:59:53,589
That Perico who got his
head broken for liar.

972
00:59:54,090 --> 00:59:56,490
I would say that I was
sent away, wasn't I?

973
00:59:56,793 --> 00:59:58,886
But you found your cage...

974
00:59:59,095 --> 01:00:02,223
Not that much. Just ask me to
go, and I'll go with you.

975
01:00:02,732 --> 01:00:05,030
Look, don't start
with that crap!

976
01:00:05,368 --> 01:00:07,802
